Rating: 4
The recipe as written is excellent, and I highly recommend it. I have also adapted it to a quick mid-week meal or weekend lunch by using leftover steak, sliced, and placed atop the salad with the blue cheese. I use the store prepared mixed greens in this case, omit the radicchio, use the pear if I have it, and add dried fruit, walnuts or sliced almonds as my mood dictates.

Rating: 4
I make this CONSTANTLY. It is one of the best dishes on this site BY FAR!! Don't alter it a bit unless you can't find a ripe pear. In that case, an apple substitutes nicely!

Rating: 4
This recipe is incredible and SO EASY. I cook a lot of steak and nothing has ever turned out so well. I seasoned the steaks and let them sit for about an hour before cooking. Also, I substituted arugula for radicchio. The dressing has the perfect acidity and sweet to go with the steak.

